                <ab>
                    MINISTER
                    OF
                    <supplied>FOREIGN</supplied>AFFAIRS
                </ab>
                
                <ab>
                    PROTOCOL
                </ab>
                
                <ab>
                    FRENCH REPUBLIC
                </ab>
                
                <ab>
                    Paris, August 6th        1888.
                </ab>
                
                <p>
                    Mister Admiral and dear colleague,
                    
                    I have the honor of informing you that Mr. Réne
                    Durecu Potin has just been named Vice-Consul of the
                    United States of America in Gorée-Dakar to fill in as
                    the Consul in case of absence or impediment.
                </p>
                
                <p>
                    I urge you, following custom,
                    to invite Mr. Governor of Senegal to take
                    the necessary measures so that this officer is
                    admitted to free exercise of his functions at least
                    unless there is some objection to raise
                    against the nomination of Mr. Durecu Potin.
                </p>
                
                <p>
                    Accept, Mister Admiral and dear colleague,
                    the new assurances of my highest consideration.
                </p>
                
                <p>
                    For the Minister, by authorization:
                    S. The plenpotentiary Minister, Director,
                    Le principal Assistant <unclear>ffour</unclear> of Under-Chief. <!-- This section is stamped -->
                </p>
                
                <p>
                    Armand <unclear/> <!-- Signature -->
                </p>
                
